race.comment: Some progressive mares lining up here, including WILD WINNER (1) who rarely runs poorly. She stuck on OK in a race dominated on speed last time and she's sure to strip fitter second-up. The rise to 1400m looks suitable and the claim gets her in with a winnable weight. FALANGHINA (2) is another that has run well in stronger races than this. She was brilliant first up then below par last time when she got a long way out of her ground. Forgive that and back her in to improve into the top three. COCKATOO ROSE (3) is a mare on the up, having won two from four this campaign. She'll be tucked up behind the speed and will be around the mark. SEA OF LIGHTS (4) draws well and looks ready to peak out to 1400m. Include her in exotics. HIGH GARDEN (5) is another that can run in the minor money.
